ing-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">We believe </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Public Service Broadcast</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ing is, and should be, the framework which drives</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> the creation of new, innovat</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ive and creative content, which </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">caters to a wide variety of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">tastes and interests</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> In this the BBC is a world leader.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; padding-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">he BBC is a major </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">commissioner of mu</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">sic </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and therefore pro</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">vides important opportunities for UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> composers and songwriters</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> and their works.  In addition, t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">he BBC’s orchestras play a vital role in supporting composers of newly commissioned music</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> by perfor</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ming it</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> in live concer</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ts and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> recording it</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> for inclusion in programmes that are broadcast, so ensuring that the composer’s work enjoys the best possible exposure to audiences. Its role in commissioning, performing and broadcasting music has positioned the BBC at the heart of the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Briti</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">sh music scene and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">highlights the important role the BBC has in the UK creative industries as a whole. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">What scope, scale and remit should the BBC have? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; padding-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">As we noted above the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">BBC</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> principle purpose should be</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> to provide content and services</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> reflect the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">diverse range of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">tastes </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and interest</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">licence fee payers.  In many areas we believe they successfu</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">lly achieve this. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">For example, t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">he BBC’s radio services</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">provide listeners access to a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">n incredibly </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">wide </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and diverse </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">rang</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">e of music -</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">classical music on Radio 3 and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Asian music on the Asian </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Network</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> while 6Music provides an invaluable platform to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">new and em</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">erging music creators</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; padding-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">However, a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">s the Committee </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">notes in its introduction to this inquiry </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">the media industry has evolved consider</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ably </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">over the last ten year </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">if anything more, rather than less, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">change</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> is likely </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">over t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">he next decade</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Therefore, w</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">e believe the BBC needs the flexibility and control of its own services i</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">n order to ensure its can continue</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> to meet new demands and cons</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">umer expectations.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  Therefore, we support the principle</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">that the BBC Trust, rather than the Government, should have responsibility for determining the type </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and remit of the BBC’s services;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">sub</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ject of course to consideration </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">of the wider market impact throu</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">gh the Public Interest Test.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; padding-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">In respect of the balance between in-house production and independent commissioning we again believe this should be a matter for the BBC itself to determine.  On the basis that innovation and creativity should be promoted an</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">d secured over any protectionism of internal processes.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  In this context we welcome the introduction of the WOCC (Window</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> of Creative Competition</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">) in the last Charter.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">How have the BBC’s commercial activities during the current Charter fitted with the BBC</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">’s public purposes and have the achieved an adequate return for </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">licence</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> fee payers?  What should the aims, scope and scale of such activities beyond 2016?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33pt; padding-left:3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">The BBC is one o</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">f the greatest content creators and delivers</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> in the world and as such provides a unique showcase for the UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">’s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> creative industries.  Where there is value in exploiting their content internationally this should be pursued for the benefit of UK creators and licence fee payers.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">PRS for Music</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, on behalf</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> of the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">rightsholders</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> we represent, benefits for the effective exploitation of BBC works where our rights have been employed.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  Therefore, support the strengthening of BBC Worldwide and its objectives to realise the commercial potential of the BBC’s content</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">What role should the BBC play in developing technology and new ways of distributing content?</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">The BBC has been instrumental in the development of many key technologies in</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> recent years</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, including </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Freeview</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">iPlayer</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">RadioPlayer</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.  These initiat</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ives have ensured the availability to consumers of affordable technologies which have importantly preserved the principles of TV and radio which is free at the point of access. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">However, t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">here is obviously </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">a balance to be struck </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">whenever the BBC invests f</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">unds from the licence fee into the development of technology services, as it can impact of the development of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">equivalent </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">commercial services.  However, where such activities are in the best interests of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> BBC, commercial content providers and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">licence fee</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> payers, we believe the BBC should have a leading role in the development of technologies and distribution services</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> which support the UK’s creative industries</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> as a whole</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">How should the BBC be funded beyond 2016? How should the BBC be governed, regulated </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and held accountable beyond 2016?  </span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">believe the BBC is at its most creative and successful when it has certainty of its governance and funding.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">  Therefore, we support the continuation of a 10 year Royal Charter as an appropriate mechanism to provide a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">framework for the BBC’s operation</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">We also support the continuation of the licence fee as the preferred means of funding the BBC.  Funding through general taxation will only provide greater conflicts between its impartiality and the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">political</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> agenda, whi</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">le funding through advertising will only serve to reduce the effectiveness of the BBC and of those who are currently funded through commercial means.  However, we believe the level of the licence fee must be representative of the ambitions and expectati</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">ons</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> which are placed on the BBC.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>